[{"id":"VH909828","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram labeled “Figure 1.” A circle of diameter “D” has a string attached with a length of “l.” The string extends from the right side of the circle. At the end of the string is a circle labeled “M.” The angle formed between the string and the circle is labeled “theta.”\" height=\"187\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH909828.g01.png\" width=\"220\" /></div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a force diagram labeled “Figure 2,” and consists of two arrows extending from a point. The first arrow labeled “T,” is long and points upward and to the left. The second arrow labeled “F sub g,” is short and points vertically downward.\" height=\"174\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH909828.g03.png\" width=\"59\" /></div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram labeled “Figure 3.” An arrow points to the left and is labeled “a sub centripetal.”\" height=\"75\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH909828.g04.png\" width=\"85\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A solid disk of diameter <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow></math></span></span> spins counterclockwise about its center at a constant speed. One end of a string of length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"l\"><math alttext=\"l\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow></math></span></span> is attached to the edge of the disk with the other end attached to an object of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M\"><math alttext=\"M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow></math></span></span>. At time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t sub 0\"><math alttext=\"t sub 0\" overflow=\"